Version 0.10.1
Update README.rst mentioning pip

Cache mass and cost of designs

When called with
  python3 -m runpy kspalculator 1055 3400:11.77:1 -b -R small -g -c -e
20.8 % of the time has been spent in Design.get_cost(), and 55.2 % of
the time has been spent in Design.get_mass().

There have been unnecessary calls to Design.get_mass() to simply
determine payload and engine mass, which are removed.

Both Design.get_mass() and Design.get_cost() are called many times
during Design evaluation/comparision, i.e. Design.is_better_than().
With above mentioned change, these methods are not called until Design
creation is completed, i.e. mass and cost do not change between calls.
Thus, it is not necessary to newly compute these values on each call.
Now, the return value is cached.

Time spent in Design.get_mass() and Design.get_cost() drops to almost
zero; Above call of kspalculator returns within less than one fourth of
the time needed earlier.

This commit should also fix computation deadline exceeded errors in our
web frontend at https://kspalculator.appspot.com/

Dont compare designs w/ ones already known as bad

This reduces calls to Design.is_better_than(), which on some calls
consumed more than 50 % of total execution time. With this commit,
latency is almost halfed.
